title: Apple Reports Record Q4 Earnings, Stock Surges
content: Apple Inc. reported record quarterly earnings that beat Wall Street expectations, driven by strong iPhone 15 sales and growing services revenue.

title: Tesla Stock Drops on Production Concerns
content: Tesla shares fell 5% after the company announced potential production delays at its new factory due to supply chain issues.

title: Microsoft Azure Revenue Exceeds Expectations
content: Microsoft Corporation saw strong growth in its cloud computing division, with Azure revenue growing 30% year-over-year.

title: Google Faces New Regulatory Challenges
content: Alphabet Inc. is facing increased regulatory scrutiny in Europe over its advertising practices and market dominance.

title: Amazon Prime Day Breaks Sales Records
content: Amazon.com Inc. announced that its annual Prime Day event generated over $12 billion in sales, setting a new company record.
